Zhou Qunfei was born into poverty in a village in rural China . 
  She worked in a factory making glass for watches until she set up her own company . 
  The 45-year-old has been named China's richest woman after her company Lens Technology went public . 
  Her company supplies protective window glass used in Apple devices . 
  She is now wealthier than Richard Branson . 
  Her mother died when she was five and her father was nearly blinded . 
 